And get used to this terminology because we will be using it a lot! Object: What you are interacting with such as the bot. Method: What you want the object to do such as move. Terminator: Ends the command.
You may have to use more than one command to reach the exit. If you fail, press the 'Reset' button to try again. You may also view these instructions again by pressing the 'Instructions' button.

data.value:
Sounds easy enough right? The problem is someone’s been jabbing the buttons too hard on the remote control and now it is broken, so we are going to have to use the manual override on the computer to get this little robot moving.
So here is what you need to know. You see that big white box underneath where it says 'Input:'? That is where you will type to program the robot. Select the bot object by typing 'bot' and Move it using the 'Move()' method. Seperate the object and method using a '.'. You may only use one command per line and don’t forget to end the command with terminator (a semicolon ‘;’). data.value: Welcome to Code_Bot. Your objective is to guide this little robot through the maze to get to the exit. Try not to crash into walls. We have plenty of spare robots so you can try again if you do. But we will not complete our mission if you crash them all.
